The paper deals with facial landmark detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of a generative adversarial module, which is a popular technique in deep learning (cs.LG). The authors also mention the use of neural networks for training the landmark detector, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper involves the processing of images, which is a common task in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the authors mention the use of a duet of original and style-aggregated images to train the landmark detector, which involves the use of multiple inputs and can be considered a form of neural ensemble (cs.NE).
